ike the law?  Do something to try and get it changed.  I'm guessing if there weren't a damn good reason for such a law, the ACLU would be all over it.<br>
<br>
Kerai, you're way off as well.  I said nothing about hi blocking anything.  I was talking about ALL the OTHER protests that went on.  Don't recall anyone being arrested for peacefully protesting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1256<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/03 3:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Freedom of Speech</span><hr size=1> Honestly, I have mixed feelings on this one.<br>
<br>
In general, I support the right of people to speak their minds and protest in public places.<br>
<br>
However, I can also see the argument for why the secret service can set up small zones around the president to protect him.<br>
<br>
However, if you are going to do that, make sure that anyone in those zones is prosecuted equally for trespassing.  (I don't know if he was the only one in this &quot;zone&quot; or not.)  Holding a sign up shouldn't make you more subject to prosecution on grounds of trespassing.  If it did, then I don't support it.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mrbanderas>Mr Banderas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 621<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/03 3:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Freedom of Speech</span><hr size=1> Linale, there's MANY laws that exist that are not enforced.  In Florida it's illegal for a woman to eat a lollipop on Sundays.  Just because it's some obscure, unused law doesn't make it right to enforce it.  Especially to a person that has no history of any type of detrimental crimes.  The only reason he was arrested the first time was for nearly exactly the same crime, and it sounds like it was just as ridiculous now as it was then.<br>
<br>
Again, I don't see any way which anyone can honestly say they're defending the government's right here in what they did.  I merely think you're arguing just to argue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1260<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/03 3:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Freedom of Speech</span><hr size=1> The key idea here for me is this...<br>
<br>
If this zone is universally enforced regardless of whether a man is holding a sign up or not as a security measure to protect the president, then I have no problem with it.<br>
<br>
If people who are holding up signs are targeted out of a large crowd as &quot;trespassers&quot; because they are holding up signs unfavorable to the president, then I believe it is a violation of freedom of speech.<br>
<br>
It's unclear from the article which of these is the case.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=linale>Linale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/03 3:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Freedom of Speech</span><hr size=1> Ammelen brings up a good point.  How big is this zone they set up?  How close was this guy trying to get to the president?  Was he within spitting distance?  Trying to force the sign into his view?<br>
<br>
That was kinda my point before.  There's probably more to the story than what's being told.  Someone eating a friggin lilipop has nothing to do with the security of the president. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammerique>Ammerique</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 461<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/03 4:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Freedom of Speech</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The veteran protester was arrested last October for trespassing at the Columbia Metropolitan Airport as he held a sign (“No War for Oil”) while waiting for George Bush to arrive. <br>
<br>
Shortly after his most recent arrest, the trespassing charge against Mr Bursey was also dropped. But in March the local US attorney, Strom Thurmond junior, suddenly brought federal charges against Mr Bursey under a little-known law that allows the Secret Service to restrict access to areas the president is visiting.<br>
<br>
Indeed, it is extremely hard to see why Mr Thurmond has picked on Mr Bursey out of all the people in the Secret Service zone. None of the other protesters with him was arrested. Neither were any of the several hundred supporters of the president who were holding equally dangerous (but pro-Bush) signs as they stood near the hangar where the president was to speak.<br>
<br>
The prosecutors say that Mr Bursey was not in a special “free-speech zone” that was set up for protesters half a mile from the hangar. The pro-Bush people did not need to be there because they were not protesting. Mr Bursey told the cops, defiantly, that he was under the impression that the whole of America was a free-speech zone.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, so from my understanding he was arrested in October for trespassing in which the charge was subsequently dropped and then in MARCH, Strom Thurmond decides to go after him using an archaic law.<br>
<br>
I find it hard to think this man was protesting more than 15 feet away from anyone else.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1261<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/03 4:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Freedom of Speech</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I find it hard to think this man was protesting more than 15 feet away from anyone else.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
SOMETHING out of the ordinary must have happened.  Even if you assume that the people in power here are evil and desire to suppress any and all free speech that goes against their views, you just don't see this happening on a daily basis to the thousands of people that are always there protesting wherever the president might be.<br>
<br>
He had to do something to get someone's attention, whether it was getting closer, being obnoxious or vocal, etc.  Otherwise, why him and not all the other protesters you see all the time?<br>
<br>
I'm not saying that the government is necessarily right here, I'm really not sure and I don't think I have enough information.  What I am saying is that if he managed to be the 1 protester this year to get noticed by a Senator and the US Attorney General, he had to have done something out of the ordinary.<br>
